flowRoot.flowPara: When there are no collections, the dialog has a special state.
Pressing a row selects/deselects a collection.
When renaming, the row becomes a text entry, other rows are insensitive, and an action bar displayes cancel and done controls.
After a collection is removed, the row is replaced with a placeholder that includes an undo button.
The first collection is automatically selected after creation.
Rows are ordered according to time/date created (newest first).
Add button becomes sensitive when the new collection field contains a valid collection name.
Further actions are available through the disclosure triangle.
